    title = {The {Dynamics} of {Income} {Inequality} in {China}, {Germany}, the {UK}, and the {US}},
    url = {https://paa.confex.com/paa/2017/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/14305},
    abstract = {We examine short-term income mobility in China, Germany, the UK, and the US. Consistent with previous research, we show that income inequality in China is at a much higher level than even the US which, in turn, is more unequal than the UK and Germany. We then show that China also has much higher level of income mobility than the three Western countries. As income mobility tends to reduce snapshot measures of income inequality, this might have implications for the true level of income inequality of the four countries. By using a simple random effects model of permanent--transitory income, we show that China has higher level of permanent income inequality than the other countries in our sample. At the same time, the variance of transitory income is also much higher in China than in the West. We end by exploring the determinants of the permanent and the transitory components of income in the four countries.},
